Base-map cartography
--------------------
- Natural Earth (PUBLIC DOMAIN) — https://www.naturalearthdata.com/
  Coastlines, admin-0 boundary lines, land polygons, rivers, lakes
  (ne_110m_*, ne_50m_rivers_lake_centerlines). Distributed via the public-domain
  nvkelso/natural-earth-vector project. Attribution given as courtesy.
- world-atlas (Natural Earth, PUBLIC DOMAIN) — https://github.com/topojson/world-atlas
  countries-110m / land-110m TopoJSON used by the earth2d renderer for the land
  fill + country borders (with a jsDelivr CDN copy as last-resort fallback).
- Land/sea masks (assets/earth/mask/*) are rasterized from Natural Earth land
  polygons — same public-domain source/license.

Earth-system data sources (live layers + representative grids)
--------------------------------------------------------------
The Planet Health Score domains and globe layers are derived from open
scientific datasets. Each carries its provider's license; the representative
grids bundled here are coarsened/derived snapshots for offline rendering.

- NOAA OISST V2.1 / Coral Reef Watch — sea-surface temperature, anomaly,
  bleaching alert area (U.S. Government work, open).
- NASA FIRMS — active fire / thermal anomalies (open).
- CAMS (Copernicus Atmosphere Monitoring Service) — particulates (PM2.5),
  NO2, dust AOD (Copernicus open license).
- GLAD / Hansen Global Forest Change (VCF5KYR) — tree-cover / forest loss
  (CC BY 4.0).
- Open-Meteo / Open-Meteo Marine — supporting meteorological + marine fields
  (CC BY 4.0).
- NOAA GFS — wind, CAPE, apparent-temperature inputs (U.S. Government work, open).
- IUCN / WDPA — protected-area coverage (WDPA terms; non-commercial-sensitive
  attributes are NOT surfaced — coverage signal only).
- GBIF — biodiversity occurrence signal (CC BY-NC for derived clustered points).
- Global Human Modification (gHM) index — human-pressure domain (CC BY 4.0).
- WRI Global Power Plant Database v1.3.0 — power-plant points (CC BY 4.0).
- Maus et al. global mining polygons v2 (PANGAEA) — extraction-site points
  (CC BY 4.0).
- Climate TRACE — industrial-site / business-footprint emitters (CC BY 4.0).
- PeeringDB — data-center facility points (open / CC-BY-style).
- WGMS — glacier summary (open, attribution).
- Berkeley Carbon Trading Project (VCM registry) — carbon-offset project points.

